text: Urania brasiliensis is a day-flying moth of the family Uraniidae first described by William John Swainson in 1833. ==Distribution== Urania brasiliensis is found in the Atlantic forest of Brazil. It is one of the two species of genus Urania found in that country.Insetos do Brasil ==References== ==External links== * *Uraniidae - Yale University Category:Uraniidae Category:Moths described in 1833
